&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong data-olk-copy-source=&quot;MailCompose&quot;&gt;Associate Director – Project Management / Delivery&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Anchanto&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;Anchanto is a global B2B SaaS company enabling enterprises, retailers, and logistics providers to manage their end-to-end eCommerce and supply chain operations through cutting-edge cloud and AI-driven platforms. With a presence across APAC and beyond, Anchanto supports over 7,000 customers and integrates with 135+ commerce and carrier platforms, driving scalable growth and operational excellence.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;The Associate Director – Delivery is a business-critical leadership role responsible for owning and scaling Anchanto’s Delivery Vertical across regions.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;This role goes beyond project execution. It owns delivery outcomes, revenue realization, customer experience, and operational scalability. You will drive predictable delivery, enforce governance, and build a high-performing delivery organization that can support Anchanto’s global growth.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;You will lead a team of Delivery Managers, own portfolio health, act as the escalation anchor, and represent Anchanto in customer and internal leadership forums.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1. Delivery Ownership &amp;amp; Business Accountability&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the end-to-end delivery portfolio across APAC/EMEA from post-sales handover to go-live and hypercare&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be accountable for revenue realization, timelines, scope adherence, and customer outcomes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive forecast accuracy and delivery predictability across all engagements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure delivery is aligned to commercial commitments and contractual milestones&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2. Portfolio Governance &amp;amp; Execution Excellence&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish and enforce strong delivery governance frameworks (Playbooks, RACI, Gates)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive visibility of portfolio health (RAG, ARR at risk, phase bottlenecks) to leadership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure no uncontrolled slippage - enforce scope, timeline, and quality discipline&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Standardize delivery practices to create a repeatable, scalable execution model&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;3. Cross-Functional Alignment &amp;amp; Execution Control&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own alignment across Sales, Solutioning, Product, Engineering, QA, and Customer Success&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure strong handoffs from Sales → Solutioning → Delivery to eliminate ambiguity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively identify and resolve execution bottlenecks and dependencies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Engineering leadership to ensure capacity and delivery feasibility alignment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;4. Customer Leadership &amp;amp; Escalation Management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as the senior escalation owner for critical accounts and delivery risks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build strong relationships with customer leadership and enterprise stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead SteerCo and governance forums, representing Anchanto’s delivery position&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure transparent communication, expectation setting, and trust-building&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;5. Delivery Transformation &amp;amp; Scale&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive initiatives to improve delivery efficiency, aut

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div data-olk-copy-source=&quot;MailCompose&quot;&gt;The Role:&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;The Associate Integration Architect is responsible for designing and delivering integration solutions. The role&lt;br&gt;involves understanding business requirements, defining integration workflows, and ensuring successful&lt;br&gt;implementation. It acts as a bridge between business, customers, and engineering teams to deliver scalable&lt;br&gt;and efficient solutions.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Engage with customers to understand business use cases, system landscape, and integration requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct functional and technical discovery sessions to identify integration touchpoints and constraints&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Engage in pre-sales discussions to understand customer systems, technical constraints, and integration requirements, and contribute to solution design&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform API feasibility analysis to assess compatibility between customer systems and platform capabilities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design high-level integration solutions across interfaces such as REST APIs, XML APIs, Kafka, SFTP, SQS, etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with product, engineering, and business teams to define scalable and future-ready solutions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide solution approaches, estimations, and technical inputs during requirement discussions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define end-to-end integration workflows, including data flow, transformation logic, and orchestration&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create detailed API and data mappings aligning customer systems with platform APIs (e.g., Anchanto APIs)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design parameter-level mappings and transformation rules to ensure accurate data exchange&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and implement appropriate integration patterns (real-time, batch, event-driven)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure solutions meet scalability, performance, and security standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare Solution Design Documents (SDDs) covering architecture, workflows, and mappings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct grooming sessions with engineering teams to ensure clarity on solution design and implementation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a bridge between customer stakeholders and internal engineering teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support development, testing, and go-live by resolving integration and design-related challenges&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Validate integration flows and assist in troubleshooting issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyse existing integrations, recommend improvements, and support enhancements or changes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Extract and understand integration logic from existing codebases when required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Skills &amp;amp; Competencies&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of API-based integrations and system interoperability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with integration patterns (real-time, asynchronous, event-driven, batch)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience with REST APIs, API design, and backend technologies (e.g., Java)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with Kafka, SQS, and file-based integrations like SFTP&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to design data mappings, transformations, and integration workflows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong problem-solving and analytical skills for complex integration scenarios&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good understanding of scalability, performance, and security considerations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Effective communication skills to work with both technical and business stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to translate business requirements into practical, scalable solutions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position (Minimum) Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Anchanto:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a Global B2B cloud company that enables enterprises and partners to grow and manage their end-to-end Commerce and Logistics operations through its world class Cloud and AI products and services. With more than 7,000 customers, leading global brands, large retailers, and postal operators leverage Anchanto to process more than a billion dollars of revenue each year. Our powerful, scalable products deliver rapid innovation integrated to over 135 different commerce and carrier platforms across the world. Our offices are spread across Singapore, Kuala Lumpur (Malaysia), Jakarta (Indonesia), Manila (Philippines), Sydney (Australia), Bangkok (Thailand), Seoul (South Korea), Pune (India). Our diverse and multicultural fabric is woven in a way that each Anchanter gets complete freedom and opportunity to realize &amp;amp; explore his/her full potential. We pride ourselves in building awesome &amp;amp; powerful products that have the potential to change the way businesses perceive eCommerce management. We believe in delivering anchanting experiences and aim to become the #1 customer-centric company in our domain.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong data-olk-copy-source=&quot;MailCompose&quot;&gt;Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;Anchanto’s OMS is a core product that enables customers to manage orders across multiple sales channels, fulfillment nodes, and operational workflows. As omni-channel commerce becomes more complex, customers expect the OMS to support not only order capture, but also orchestration across marketplaces, webstores, stores, warehouses, and partner ecosystems. This requires strong capabilities in order lifecycle management, allocation, inventory visibility, fulfillment coordination, returns, exchanges, customer promise management, and integrations.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;Anchanto needs an OMS Business Analyst who can work closely with the Product Manager and independently drive requirement analysis, workflow detailing, analytics, documentation, and execution support. This role is essential to ensure requirements are complete, clear, testable, and aligned with real-world retail and omni-channel operations.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategy&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the Product Manager in converting product strategy into structured backlogs and execution-ready requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze customer pain points, workflow gaps, and operational challenges across omni-channel retail use cases.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support requirement discovery for OMS capabilities such as order capture, fulfillment orchestration, store fulfillment, inventory visibility, returns, and exchanges.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use analytics, product usage, and customer feedback to identify product gaps and improvement opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Execution&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Write business requirements, user stories, workflows, use cases, edge cases, and acceptance criteria for OMS capabilities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Independently drive requirement discussions and structure ambiguous business needs with minimal direction from the Product Manager.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define functional requirements and support NFR discussions covering usability, reliability, auditability, configurability, and scale.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with Engineering and QA through design, development, testing, rollout, and release stabilization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in API requirement discussions and define expectations for validations, status handling, mappings, event flows, exceptions, retry behavior, and business rules.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review requirements for completeness, consistency, and implementation readiness, and track dependencies and clarifications through execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&l

&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;About Anchanto:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Anchanto helps all businesses to exploit the full potential of e-commerce. Our suite of SaaS Products enables companies globally to springboard omnichannel sales, scale fulfilment operations, and use intelligent data to grow their e-commerce, logistics &amp;amp; warehousing activities. Leading, brands, distributors, retailers, and logistic enterprises such as L&#39;Oréal, Decathlon, or DHL Supply Chain rely on our technology to scale their local and global e-commerce operations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong data-olk-copy-source=&quot;MailCompose&quot;&gt;Business Analyst – WMS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;The Business Analyst – WMS will work closely with the Product Manager to analyze business problems, define product requirements, support execution, and drive analytics-led insights for the WMS product. The role requires strong WMS domain understanding, experience in writing structured requirements, and the ability to independently drive workstreams with minimal direction.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;The ideal candidate should be comfortable handling requirement gathering, workflow analysis, documentation, dashboarding, product usage analysis, stakeholder coordination, and customer-facing validation activities. The person should also have hands-on exposure to analytics and product insight tools such as Mixpanel, Pendo etc. to support measurement, feature adoption analysis, and product decision-making.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategy&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the Product Manager in translating product strategy into structured requirement backlogs and execution-ready inputs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in problem discovery, feature shaping, and business process analysis for WMS capabilities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze customer and operational pain points to identify product gaps and improvement opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use data and workflow understanding to support prioritization discussions and roadmap refinement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute insights on feature adoption, usage behavior, and process bottlenecks to guide better product decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Execution&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Write detailed business requirements, user stories, functional flows, process maps, use cases, edge cases, and acceptance criteria.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Independently drive requirement discussions with stakeholders and bring structure to ambiguous business needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review workflows and ensure requirements are complete, testable, and aligned to intended business outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support definition of non-functional requirements such as usability, performance, scalability, auditability, and reliability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in API review discussions and define business requirements for validations, mappings, status flows, exceptions, and operational behavior.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with Engineering and QA during development and testing to clarify requirements and resolve open questions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure requirement traceability from business problem to delivered solution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work as a strong independent contributor within the product team and take ownership of assigned modules or workstreams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the Product Manager in maintaining requirement quality, follow-up discipline, and execution governance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help junior team members or cross-functional stakeholders understand workflows, business rules, and documentation standards where needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive assigned deliverables proactively without dependency on constant direction.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
