&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reporting:&lt;/strong&gt; Pro

&lt;p&gt;We at &lt;strong&gt;Anchanto &lt;/strong&gt;are seeking an experienced Database Administrator to join our team responsible for developing database solutions. The right candidate will energize the team, foster collaboration across the organization, and lead the drive toward high-caliber, high-performing products&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop database solutions by designing proposed system, defining database physical structure and functional capabilities, security, back-up, and recovery specifications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Configure RDS services, create &amp;amp; manage documentation for the configurations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Troubleshoot DB Server outages, errors, slowness as they occur, including some after-hours and weekend support as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Configure DB monitoring utilities to help communicate risks proactively.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Determine the most effective way to increase performance and recommend hardware upgrades, server configuration changes, or index/query changes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop/configure monitoring solutions to continuously monitor DB performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with development teams to understand their needs and propose most optimal physical implementations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Configure database in the high-availability clustering mode and/or on cloud as necessary.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be the in-house expert for DB administration best practices including data backup and retrieval.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must be able to learn various database technologies such as MySQL, Postgres and NoSQL databases.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You need to have/ Required skills:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must have at least 5 years of hands on experience as a DBA.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must have strong database administration skills such as backup, performance monitoring, resource management, DB tuning, user rights, scheduling jobs, monitoring jobs, reading an interpreting SQL logs etc. either in MySQL or Postgres or both. Role requires to work on both databases as well NoSQL databases in future.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must have excellent knowledge of Data modelling and design.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must have strong knowledge and hands on expertise in stored procedures, functions, triggers, indexes, jobs and performance tuning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must have strong knowledge of AWS RDS services · Knowledge of reporting tools is a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with Data Warehouse and BI systems is also a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prior experience with building high performance e-commerce software is also a big plus.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Enabling Simpler, Faster and Scalable eCommerce Operations, Our mission is to simplify backend eCommerce operations for businesses of all sizes through our innovative &amp;amp; intelligent SaaS platforms. We aim to transform the way businesses conduct eCommerce in the region, while aggressively moving towards becoming the most customer-centric company in our domain.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;With headquarters in Singapore, a Global Product Engineering Centre in Pune, India and with strong local presence in the countries we do business in, Anchanto team numbers more than 300 employees worldwide serving 300+ customers worldwide. With rapidly growing customer base and constantly evolving needs of the market, we are looking to ramp up our engineering teams in Pune.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are looking to work with a fast-growing product company that offers to work on cutting edge technology, exhilarating &amp;amp; rewarding experience and excellent work-life balance, take a look at our various job openings.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role (Describe the role):&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As Project Manager, you will play a pivotal role in Anchanto’s global delivery organisation. You will be responsible for managing full lifecycle projects for our global customers from initiation to Go-Live, ensuring revenue unblocking, meeting customer satisfaction (CSAT) and Net Promoter Score (NPS) goals, and delivering on time, within scope, and within budget.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and manage project scope, objectives, and key deliverables in collaboration with stakeholders and senior management.&lt;br&gt;• Develop and maintain detailed project plans (schedules, budgets, resources, communications) and ensure adherence as the project evolves.&lt;br&gt;• Lead and coordinate cross-functional teams (internal, external clients, vendors) to achieve milestones and deliverables.&lt;br&gt;• Proactively manage project risks and issues; implement mitigation plans and escalate when necessary.&lt;br&gt;• Monitor and report project progress—budget, schedule, quality, scope, and stakeholder satisfaction—as the single point of contact (SPOC) for customers.&lt;br&gt;• Manage multiple client relationships simultaneously to ensure strong outcomes, effective communication, and high customer satisfaction (CSAT/NPS).&lt;br&gt;• Ensure Go-Live readiness, smooth transition to support or operations, and complete project closure including lessons learned.&lt;br&gt;• Align project execution with organisational strategies and revenue objectives to support global customer delivery and success.&lt;br&gt;• Build and maintain strong customer relationships, negotiating effectively and independently leading stakeholder meetings.&lt;br&gt;• Drive end-to-end project delivery with strict adherence to schedule, cost, and quality standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum 5 years’ experience as a Project Manager in the Supply Chain domain within large global enterprises.&lt;br&gt;• Proven ability to manage complex, multi-stakeholder projects with a focus on Logistics/Supply Chain.&lt;br&gt;• Demonstrated expertise in creating and managing project plans, tracking deliverables, and proactively managing risks to achieve both short- and long-term goals.&lt;br&gt;• Experience delivering and supporting end-to-end engagements in the Supply Chain domain.&lt;br&gt;• Excellent written, verbal, and negotiation skills.&lt;br&gt;• Strong stakeholder management skills.&lt;br&gt;• Proven track record of successfully managing multiple concurrent projects.&lt;br&gt;• PMP or equivalent project management certification is a plus.&lt;br&gt;• Proficient in French language.&lt;br&gt;• Immediate joiners preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Personal Attributes:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Outcome-focused and results-driven project management professional.&lt;br&gt;• Solution-oriented thinker with a strategic, big-picture perspective and attention to detail.&lt;br&gt;• Resilient and composed in navigating complex or challenging situations.&lt;br&gt;• Highly organised, with the ability to prioritise and manage multiple tasks effectively.&lt;br&gt;• Collaborative mindset with strong ethics and a values-driven individual.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Description: Software Engineering Manager at Anchanto India&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
